article.headline: Seton Hall 85, Rutgers 58
article.story: EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Andre Barrett had 20 points and nine assists to lead a balanced attack and Seton Hall scored its second biggest win in its long New Jersey rivalry with Rutgers with an 85-58 victory on Saturday night. The 27-point margin of victory was surpassed only by a 109-81 win in 1986, and this one had the predominantly Seton Hall crowd of 15,253 chanting "We Own Jersey" during the second half. The Pirates (15-5, 5-3 Big East) shot 54.7 percent from the field for the game and had five players in double figures scoring in bouncing back from a disappointing road loss at West Virginia earlier this week. J.R. Morris added 18 points, John Allen had 17, Andre Sweet 15 and Kelly Whitney 10 points and 11 rebounds as the Pirates ended Rutgers' all-time best four-game winning streak in the conference. Herve Lamizana and Ricky Shields had 14 points apiece to lead Rutgers (13-7, 5-5). Quincy Douby added 13 for the Scarlet Knights, who shot 32.8 percent from the field, including just 20.8 from 3-point range (5 of 24).
